# Absolute path to your Claude Code data folder on the HOST machine.
# This gets mounted (read-only) into the container.
#
# macOS / Linux:
#   CLAUDE_DIR_HOST=/Users/you/.claude
#   CLAUDE_DIR_HOST=/home/you/.claude
#
# Windows (Docker Desktop) — use forward slashes:
#   CLAUDE_DIR_HOST=C:/Users/you/.claude
CLAUDE_DIR_HOST=C:/Users/you/.claude

# OPTIONAL — Claude Cowork ("local agent mode" in the desktop app). Point this at
# the desktop app's local-agent-mode-sessions folder to also track Cowork usage.
# Leave it unset if you don't use Cowork; the dashboard simply won't show it.
#
# macOS:
#   COWORK_DIR_HOST=/Users/you/Library/Application Support/Claude/local-agent-mode-sessions
# Windows (Docker Desktop) — use forward slashes:
#   COWORK_DIR_HOST=C:/Users/you/AppData/Roaming/Claude/local-agent-mode-sessions
# Linux:
#   COWORK_DIR_HOST=/home/you/.config/Claude/local-agent-mode-sessions
#
# Note: Cowork runs in *full-VM sandbox* mode keep their transcripts inside the VM,
# so only host-side local-agent sessions are captured.
#COWORK_DIR_HOST=C:/Users/you/AppData/Roaming/Claude/local-agent-mode-sessions

# OPTIONAL — AI Insights backend (the chat + per-section ✨ buttons).
# You can also configure a provider + model + API key at runtime from
# ⚙ Settings → AI Insights (stored in your browser). The options below are the
# server-side fallback used when no key is set in Settings.
#
# (a) Bundle the Claude Code CLI in the image so it can run `claude -p` using
#     your mounted ~/.claude token (uses the normal subscription, NOT the
#     rate-limited OAuth Messages API → no 429). Rebuild after changing:
#     `npm run docker:up`. Adds the CLI + ripgrep to the image.
#WITH_CLAUDE_CLI=1
#
# (b) Or use a dedicated Anthropic API key (works without the CLI):
#     Get one at https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys
#ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
#
# (c) Or route through a corporate LLM proxy (LiteLLM / gateway) using Claude
#     Code's own env vars. The token is sent as an Authorization: Bearer header;
#     the base URL must expose the Anthropic Messages format (/v1/messages):
#ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=https://litellm.company.com
#ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN=sk-litellm-...
#
# Optional model override for the server-side fallback (default claude-opus-4-8).
# Set this if your proxy doesn't serve claude-opus-4-8 (else calls 400/404):
#AI_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6

# OPTIONAL — "Actual billed" cost from a LiteLLM gateway.
# When you run Claude Code through a LiteLLM proxy, the dashboard shows the REAL
# cost billed by the gateway next to the estimate. By default it reuses your
# ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL + ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN (the virtual key is self-scoped, so it
# can read its own /user/daily/activity — no master key needed). Override only if
# the gateway/key for reading spend differs (e.g. a key with spend-view permission):
#LITELLM_BASE_URL=https://litellm.company.com
#LITELLM_API_KEY=sk-litellm-...

# OPTIONAL — Anonymous product analytics (PostHog). The dashboard sends only
# anonymous feature-usage events (which tab is opened, exports, an anonymous
# install count) — never tokens, file/project paths, session contents, or
# personal data. It is ON by default; you can also opt out at runtime from
# Settings → Telemetry. To build a fully telemetry-free image, set this to 1:
#VITE_DISABLE_ANALYTICS=1
